I think Courage is mostly on with this except the idea that most players want to run into other real players.  This is one of the main fallacies content creators spout off: they think everyone wants the game to be more competitive.  I think the exact opposite of this is true.  Most players are casual and these players tend to like a small degree of challenge which would be better suited with bot non-human opponents. We just play the pvp mode with other people because there isn't an alternative.  If there were a paid version of Fortnite with unlockable cosmetics seasonally and all bot lobbies, I'd play that 100% of the time and isolate myself from all other human players.  I'd like it to be co-op for squads to play with friends but I and everyone I know have zero interest in a more competitive experience-content  creators only have this selfish wish for their own stream view count.  I'm sure most of them enjoy the competition in addition to this as do some other players but the majority of players play games for fun and not for competitive sweaty battles.  This is plain as day, you can see it in the player count for ranked mode versus normal.

The rest of his remarks I agree with and think they would be welcome additions to bring back. His plead for no bots at the end game is something that's just way off for casuals.  I'm whistlin' Dixie if I get a bot at the end game.
